<subSubSection id="C374652CFFD5FFBED4CCFE550803FDF1" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFD5FFBED4CCFE550803FDF1" blockId="40.[151,1437,402,1366]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFD5FFBED4CCFE550C1AFD8B" bold="true" box="[199,322,510,536]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFD5FFBED5BDFE540FD6FD8B" authority="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano, 2022" authorityName="Martínez &amp; Brescovit &amp; Quijano" authorityYear="2022" box="[438,654,511,537]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="narinensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFD5FFBED5BDFE540FD6FD8B" box="[438,654,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Tenedos narinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFD5FFBED69DFE540F8FFD8A" bold="true" box="[662,727,511,537]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22957CEFFD5FFBED69DFE540F8FFD8A" box="[662,727,511,537]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, can be recognized from remain species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6E4D24FFD5FFBED0C2FE540877FD8A" baseAuthorityName="Chamberlin" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[1225,1327,511,537]" class="Arachnida" family="Zodariidae" genus="Tenedos" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="barronus">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFD5FFBED0C2FE540877FD8A" box="[1225,1327,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">barronus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by flattened, laminar, large median apophysis (MA) with short posterior extension; bifid retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA), posterior branch (pRTA) long, curved, anterior branch (aRTA) laminar-shaped (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFD5FFBED06DFDEC09B6FDF2" box="[1126,1262,582,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,181,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-19@41.[151,1436,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 25. Tenedos narinensis sp. n. A–B. Male habitus (ICN-Ar-8022): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–F. Male palp: C. Ventral view. D. Prolateral view. E. Retroventral view. F. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C–D: 200µm; E–F: 500µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520813" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520813/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Figs 25C–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFD5FFBED0F2FDEC0817FDF1" box="[1273,1359,583,610]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,188,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-27@42.[230,1356,181,1835]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 26. Tenedos wayuu sp. n. A–B. Male palp (ICN-Ar-12342): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. Tenedos narinensis sp. n. C–D. Male palp: C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–D: 200µm. Abbreviations: aMA, anterior branch of the median apophysis ApC, appendix of the conductor; C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; pRTA, posterior branch of the retrolateral tibial apophysis; RPC, retrolateral process of the cymbium; SD, spermatic ducts; T, tegulum; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520817/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">26C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C374652CFFD5FFBED4CCFDC10CC7FAA2" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD136A7FFD5FFBED4CCFDC10FB8FA9D" blockId="40.[151,1437,402,1366]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFD5FFBED4CCFDC10C01FD17" bold="true" box="[199,345,618,644]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B91AEAB5FFD5FFBED56AFDC00CC3FD16" box="[353,411,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Male</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="54D58805FFD5FFBED5A0FDC00F40FD16" box="[427,536,619,645]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Holotype</typeStatus>
, ICN-Ar-8022). Coloration (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFD5FFBED756FDC00EB2FD16" box="[861,1002,618,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,181,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-19@41.[151,1436,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 25. Tenedos narinensis sp. n. A–B. Male habitus (ICN-Ar-8022): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–F. Male palp: C. Ventral view. D. Prolateral view. E. Retroventral view. F. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C–D: 200µm; E–F: 500µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520813" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520813/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 25A–B</figureCitation>
): carapace brown, dark brown in margins; brown thoracic grooves, faint. Chelicerae with paturon brown and brown-reddish fangs. Endites light yellow. Labium and sternum light brown. Legs: Coxae I–IV light brown. Femora I–IV brown on base, yellow the rest of their extension. Patellae, metatarsi I–IV yellow. Abdomen: dorsally gray, spots pattern undistinguished, due poorly preservation of the specimen. Lateral and ventrally, dark gray. Spinnerets light yellow. Measurements: total length 5.13, carapace length 2.61, width 1.62, height 1.59. Clypeus height 0.47. Eye diameters and interdistances: AME 0.09, ALE 0.10, PME 0.11, PLE 0.11; AME–AME 0.11, AME–ALE 0.22, AME–PME 0.16, PME–PME 0.26, PME–PLE 0.32, ALE–PLE 0.25. Chelicerae 0.72 length. Sternum length 1.03, width 0.96. Legs: I—femur 2.18/ patella 0.73/ tibia 1.78/ metatarsus 1.49/ tarsus 1.14/ total 7.32; II—1.85/ 0.62/ 1.47/ 1.40/ 0.90/ 6.21; III—1.71/ 0.62/ 1.24/ 1.65/ 0.92/ 6.14; IV—2.02/ 0.84/ 1.65/ 2.49/ 1.18/ 8.18. Abdomen length 2.31. Legs spines pattern (only the differences from the general pattern): I—tibia v2-2-2, p0-1-1, metatarsus v2-2-2. Palp: retrolateral process of cymbium (RPC), long, wide; tegulum (T) large, rounded, longer than wide, retrolateral excavation few accentuated; subtegulum (St) large, longer than wide, globose, covered by embolus and conductor in ventral view; conductor developed, wide, with short, thin sclerotized region on distal side; appendix (ApC) short, apically sharp; embolus (E) long, filiform towards apex; base of embolus (EB) approximately as long as basal tegular membrane; basal tegular membrane (BTM) originated basally on tegulum, proximally flattened, reticulated, ending as short, sharp appendix; spermatic ducts (SD) S-shaped, anterior fold full open; ventral tibial apophysis (VTA) short, quadrangular-shaped in ventral view; median apophysis (MA) large, flattened, irregular in borders; retrolateral tibial apophysis (RTA) large, almost as long as palpal tibia (
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFD5FFBED5E1FB580F2BFA9E" box="[490,627,1266,1293]" captionStart="FIGURE 25" captionStartId="41.[151,250,1869,1893]" captionTargetBox="[151,1427,181,1845]" captionTargetId="figure-19@41.[151,1436,181,1845]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURE 25. Tenedos narinensis sp. n. A–B. Male habitus (ICN-Ar-8022): A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–F. Male palp: C. Ventral view. D. Prolateral view. E. Retroventral view. F. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–B: 2mm; C–D: 200µm; E–F: 500µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520813" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520813/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Figs 25C–F</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="13552A22FFD5FFBED675FB580F8CFA9D" box="[638,724,1267,1294]" captionStart="FIGURE 26" captionStartId="42.[151,250,1859,1883]" captionTargetBox="[239,1351,188,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-27@42.[230,1356,181,1835]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 26. Tenedos wayuu sp. n. A–B. Male palp (ICN-Ar-12342): A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. Tenedos narinensis sp. n. C–D. Male palp: C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. Scale bars: A–D: 200µm. Abbreviations: aMA, anterior branch of the median apophysis ApC, appendix of the conductor; C, conductor; E, embolus; MA, median apophysis; pRTA, posterior branch of the retrolateral tibial apophysis; RPC, retrolateral process of the cymbium; SD, spermatic ducts; T, tegulum; VTA, ventral tibial apophysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520817" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520817/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">26C–D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
